# weave.word — what a weave IS: all of a branch's folds at a moment, the world made present.
# Axiom: it bottoms out in the host (every chain of a branch, folded at a moment). Descends from
# word.word, base.word, chain.word, branch.word, fold.word. Every word grounded (weave, fold,
# chain, branch, world). `moment` is the floor (time). The deeper world, the one beings' folds
# AGREE on, waits for `being`, the perspective that makes agreement mean anything.

A weave is all the folds of a branch at a moment, every chain folded at once.
A weave is a world, a branch whole and present.
